# Leave both of these commented out for normal use. When unset, the frontend calls relative
# paths (/api, /socket.io) which the Vite dev server proxies to the backend on localhost:5000 —
# this works automatically whether you open the app via localhost OR your machine's LAN IP
# (e.g. http://192.168.100.171:5173), with zero reconfiguration.
#
# Only set these if you're pointing the frontend at a backend running somewhere else entirely
# (a different machine, a deployed API, etc):
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
# VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000
